features: Built with cutting edge technology and with the utmost of care, Cosmo brings you beautiful premium range hoods at an affordable price. Expect cooking and cleaning experiences that make life easier, brighten up your kitchen, and protect your health.

SLIM SPACE-SAVING DESIGN: Slim profile range hood saves space. Under cabinet installation makes it great for condos and apartments. Converts ducted to ductless range hood with Carbon Filter Kit Part # CFK3-TM (Sold Separately). Suitable for top OR back venting. Dimensions: 29.5" (W) x 18.8" (D) x 5.3" (H).

EFFICIENT YET QUIET: 3-speed motor, with noise level as low as 40 dB on lowest fan speed with rigid ducting (sold separately) under optimal conditions; range hood comes with flexible ducting for convenient installation. Cosmo’s range hood filters your kitchen without the loudness and sounds of competing range hoods

SUPERIOR FILTRATION: Durable reusable aluminum mesh filters included to trap grease and oil. Multi-layer filters trap grease more effectively. 2 exhaust ports are available on range hood to fit a variety of different homes and configurations

2-YEAR LIMITED PARTS: Our customer support team is based proudly in the USA. Range Hood Product Dimensions: 29.5" (W) x 18.8" (D) x 5.3" (H). Electrical Requirements: 120V / 60Hz. 3-Prong Plug (INCLUDED). Duct Size: 4 3/4" Round
body.description: Cosmo’s new and improved COS-5U30 Under Cabinet Range Hood has modern sharp styling for any kitchen decor. Featured in brushed stainless steel, efficient airflow removes smells and odors with ease. Two aluminum mesh filters collect unwanted grease and oil from the air. Push-button controls make using hood a breeze; choose from 3 fan speeds for the right amount of suction. Built-in energy-efficient LED lighting ensures visibility for cooking at all times of the day. Convertible to ductless operation with the Carbon Filter Kit (Part # CFK3-TM)(SOLD SEPARATELY).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect in every way!
reviews.reviewText: I don't know why I waited so long to buy this! I bought the Cosmo 30" slim fit (for ductless install) and it fit perfectly. I like the modern slimline look, the two lights in the front are nice and bright and there are 3 fan speeds. Install was easy enough. It did take two people and I would recommend an extension on your drill. It's lightweight, I was able to hold it in place while my husband screwed it in. The hardest part was removing the blue packing film. The filters for the 30" Slim (CFK3-TM) are not included but in the box is a link to a form for a free filter kit in exchange for a review or you can purchase one on their website. From what I've read, the other filters do not fit so don't order the one off Amazon that is not the right one. So far I am thrilled with my purchase. It's beautiful, functional and affordable.Update: I received my free filters!!

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Performance and Sleek Design!
reviews.reviewText: Title: Excellent Performance and Sleek Design!I recently purchased the COSMO COS-5MU30 30 in. Under Cabinet Range Hood for my kitchen, and I couldn't be more pleased with its performance and design.First and foremost, the ductless convertible feature is a game-changer. It provides the flexibility to install the range hood without the need for an external duct, making it easy to fit into any kitchen setup. The slim design is perfect for saving space while still effectively removing cooking odors and smoke.The 3-speed exhaust fan is a great addition, allowing me to customize the ventilation based on the cooking activity. Whether it's a quick stir-fry or a slow simmer, this range hood has the power to handle it all. The LED lights are a fantastic touch, providing bright and energy-efficient illumination over the stovetop.The reusable filter is a practical and eco-friendly feature. It captures grease effectively and is easy to clean, saving me the hassle and cost of constantly replacing disposable filters.The stainless steel construction not only adds a touch of modern elegance to my kitchen but also ensures durability and easy maintenance. The materials used feel premium, and the overall build quality is impressive.Installation was straightforward, thanks to the clear instructions provided. The range hood operates quietly, which is a significant plus in a busy kitchen environment.In conclusion, the COSMO COS-5MU30 30 in. Under Cabinet Range Hood has exceeded my expectations. It combines functionality with a sleek design, making it a valuable addition to any kitchen. I highly recommend this product to anyone in need of a reliable and stylish range hood.

reviews.reviewTitle: easy to install, except removing the blue stuff was so hard. once installed looks and works great
reviews.reviewText: if you have older 12" deep cabinets, mounting could be tricky because you need nearly 1" for the power cord. it is feasible to adjust the plastic piece holding the power cord straight but that's a 'better know what you're doing' type issue. power is 44" long maybe in the factory, after internal routing you get about 35" (in my case)half an hour or so peeling off blue stuff and under 10 minutes to mount it.As someone looking for as simple an install as possible i scored 100% with this unit. Install was easy, i measured and drilled the holes for the front first, sat the unit on the screws (its lite enough) and quickly mounted the rear pair of screws. The front and rear have the wide holes that narrow so you can slide the hood on and off, i didnt want that and the rear has permanent holes so i used those. i was worried about vibrations and 'keeds' :)It looks nice and clean and i never thought about it but i appreciate the lack of some big stupid logo on the unit. its just the buttons and looks clean. the metal is thin but decent, doesnt bend or ding easily.The leds are nice, good amount of light, i got the 6500k to match my kitchen.The blue stuff wow, I ended up being impressed by how scratch resistant it is. its too bad they couldnt wrap my car in it.fan is good, its what i expected, its not silent but even on low the steam etc from the stove immediately flows up and out. there's a low whine, its low though so fades into the background easily. its there but low and i dont have to adjust my volumes when its on low or medium. I didnt test high, low-med gets me what i need.super happy, totally recommend.
